snippet.textDisplay:
That was an eight minute musical journey into Junoonland - a treat for every Junooni. Loved this rendition! 
Of course Junoon is incomplete without Ali Azmat and Brian but that cannot take anything away from how complete this performance was. Mannu's basswork was probably the highlight of the song. 
Miss Junoon days, how we wish Ali Azmat and Salman Ahmad can put their difference aside and just do a reunion tour for the Junoon fans out there!

snippet.textDisplay:
When are these guys gonna do a proper Junoon song with Ali and the whole crew instead of always inviting other random singers to "mix things up"? I mean no desrespect to RFAK but I just want a Junoon song sung BY Junoon in coke studio with some added touches to the music. Is that too much to ask? These guys seem to think that adding more singers with different singing styles makes everything better. It works a lot of the times. But not with Junoon. Junoon is supposed to be a ROCK band. Their songs REQUIRE a loud, bold and passionate voice like Ali Azmat!
Aisa lagta hai k yeh batain in logon k sar k uper se guzar jati hain.

Really disappointed by Studio's decision, We all know about diversity but soul of song should not be killed like this. Coke Studio U have brutally ruined the essence of Sufism by making RFAK as lead singer of this version of medley of  2 soulful songs. I was trying to find moment in the whole song which can blow my mind but never find one in it.
If asking to rate it I would in negative always without thinking.
Coke Studio team must know if U have marked a high level in all studios now U can leave a weak point which can lead U down like India's Studio. 

Ali Noor is better with Guitar in his hands rather than acting like weird hand moments I wont say the word Wise ppl know what I mean :/

Anyway one thing was good which has always been Great. Salman's Guitaring
Plz keep doing good work.
